msgid "Using ImmediateMesh"
msgstr "Ag baint úsáide as ImmediateMesh"

msgid ""
"The :ref:`ImmediateMesh <class_ImmediateMesh>` is a convenient tool to "
"create dynamic geometry using an OpenGL 1.x-style API. Which makes it both "
"approachable to use and efficient for meshes which need to be updated every "
"frame."
msgstr ""
"Is uirlis áisiúil é an :ref:`ImmediateMesh <class_ImmediateMesh>` chun "
"céimseata dhinimiciúil a chruthú ag baint úsáide as API ar stíl OpenGL 1.x. "
"Rud a fhágann go bhfuil sé sochaideartha le húsáid agus éifeachtach le "
"haghaidh mogaill ar gá gach fráma a nuashonrú."

msgid ""
"Generating complex geometry (several thousand vertices) with this tool is "
"inefficient, even if it's done only once. Instead, it is designed to "
"generate simple geometry that changes every frame."
msgstr ""
"Tá céimseata casta (roinnt mílte vertices) a ghiniúint leis an uirlis seo "
"neamhéifeachtúil, fiú mura ndéantar é ach uair amháin. Ina áit sin, tá sé "
"deartha chun geoiméadracht shimplí a ghiniúint a athraíonn gach fráma."

msgid ""
"First, you need to create a :ref:`MeshInstance3D <class_meshinstance3d>` and "
"add an :ref:`ImmediateMesh <class_ImmediateMesh>` to it in the Inspector."
msgstr ""
"Ar dtús, ní mór duit :ref:`MeshInstance3D <class_meshinstance3d>` a chruthú "
"agus :ref:`ImmediateMesh <class_ImmediateMesh>` a chur leis sa Chigire."

msgid ""
"Next, add a script to the MeshInstance3D. The code for the ImmediateMesh "
"should go in the ``_process()`` function if you want it to update each "
"frame, or in the ``_ready()`` function if you want to create the mesh once "
"and not update it. If you only generate a surface once, the ImmediateMesh is "
"just as efficient as any other kind of mesh as the generated mesh is cached "
"and reused."
msgstr ""
"Ansin, cuir script leis an MeshInstance3D. Ba chóir go rachadh an cód don "
"ImmediateMesh san fheidhm ''_process()'' más mian leat gach fráma a "
"nuashonrú, nó san fheidhm ''_ready()'' más mian leat an mogalra a chruthú "
"uair amháin agus gan é a nuashonrú. Mura ngineann tú ach dromchla uair "
"amháin, tá an ImmediateMesh chomh héifeachtach le haon chineál eile mogalra "
"agus an mogalra a ghintear i dtaisce agus athúsáidte."

msgid ""
"To begin generating geometry you must call ``surface_begin()``. "
"``surface_begin()`` takes a ``PrimitiveType`` as an argument. "
"``PrimitiveType`` instructs the GPU how to arrange the primitive based on "
"the vertices given whether it is triangles, lines, points, etc. A complete "
"list can be found under the :ref:`Mesh <class_mesh>` class reference page."
msgstr ""
"Chun tús a chur le céimseata a ghiniúint ní mór duit ``dromchla_begin()`` a "
"ghlaoch. Glacann ``dromchla_begin()`` ``PrimitiveType`` mar argóint. Tugann "
"``PrimitiveType`` treoir don GPU conas an primitive a shocrú bunaithe ar na "
"rinn a thugtar cibé acu an triantáin, línte, pointí, srl é. Is féidir liosta "
"iomlán a fháil faoin :ref:`Mogalra <class_mesh>` leathanach tagartha ranga."

msgid ""
"Once you have called ``surface_begin()`` you are ready to start adding "
"vertices. You add vertices one at a time. First you add vertex specific "
"attributes such as normals or UVs using ``surface_set_****()`` (e.g. "
"``surface_set_normal()``). Then you call ``surface_add_vertex()`` to add a "
"vertex with those attributes. For example:"
msgstr ""
"Nuair a bheidh tú ar a dtugtar ''surface_begin()'' tá tú réidh chun tús a "
"chur vertices. Cuireann tú vertices amháin ag an am. Ar dtús, cuireann tú "
"tréithe sonracha vertex ar nós gnáthaimh nó UVanna le ''surface_set_****()'' "
"(m.sh. ''surface_set_normal()''). Ansin glaonn tú ar "
"''surface_add_vertex()'' chun stuaic a chur leis na tréithe sin. Mar shampla:"

msgid ""
"Only attributes added before the call to ``surface_add_vertex()`` will be "
"included in that vertex. If you add an attribute twice before calling "
"``surface_add_vertex()``, only the second call will be used."
msgstr ""
"Ní chuirfear san áireamh sa stuaic sin ach tréithe a cuireadh leis roimh an "
"nglao ar ''surface_add_vertex()''. Má chuireann tú tréith leis faoi dhó sula "
"nglaonn tú ar ''surface_add_vertex()'', ní úsáidfear ach an dara glao."

msgid ""
"Finally, once you have added all your vertices call ``surface_end()`` to "
"signal that you have finished generating the surface. You can call "
"``surface_begin()`` and ``surface_end()`` multiple times to generate "
"multiple surfaces for the mesh."
msgstr ""
"Mar fhocal scoir, nuair a bheidh do chuid vertices go léir curtha leis, "
"glaoigh ar ''surface_end()'' chun comhartha a thabhairt go bhfuil an "
"dromchla críochnaithe agat. Is féidir leat glaoch ar ''surface_begin()'' "
"agus ''surface_end()'' arís agus arís eile chun dromchlaí éagsúla a "
"ghiniúint don mhogalra."

msgid ""
"The example code below draws a single triangle in the ``_ready()`` function."
msgstr ""
"Tarraingíonn an cód samplach thíos triantán amháin san fheidhm ''_ready()'''."

msgid ""
"The ImmediateMesh can also be used across frames. Each time you call "
"``surface_begin()`` and ``surface_end()``, you are adding a new surface to "
"the ImmediateMesh. If you want to recreate the mesh from scratch each frame, "
"call ``clear_surfaces()`` before calling ``surface_begin()``."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir an ImmediateMesh a úsáid freisin ar fud frámaí. Gach uair a "
"ghlaonn tú ar ''surface_begin()'' agus ''surface_end()'', tá dromchla nua á "
"chur agat leis an ImmediateMesh. Más mian leat an mogall a athchruthú ó thús "
"gach fráma, glaoigh ar ''clear_surfaces()'' sula nglaonn tú ar "
"''surface_begin()''."

msgid ""
"The above code will dynamically create and draw a single surface each frame."
msgstr ""
"Beidh an cód thuas a chruthú go dinimiciúil agus a tharraingt dromchla "
"amháin gach fráma."
